President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. 

- Mickey D. Barnett is nominated for Governor of the Board of Governors of the United States Postal Service. He is currently the Managing Partner of the Barnett Law Firm and has previously served in the New Mexico State Senate and as a Legislative Assistant to Senator Pete Domenici. Barnett has been a member of the Board of Governors of the United States Postal Service since 2006.

- James L. Huffman is nominated for Member of the Board of Trustees of the Morris K. Udall and Stewart L. Udall Foundation. He is currently a Visiting Fellow at the Hoover Institution and was previously a Professor of Law at Lewis and Clark Law School. Huffman has also served on the National Environmental Justice Advisory Council.

- Matthew V. Masterson is nominated for Commissioner of the Election Assistance Commission. He is currently the Deputy Chief of Staff and Chief Information Officer for the Ohio Secretary of State. Masterson has previously held multiple roles at the Election Assistance Commission and has a background in election administration.

- Christy McCormick is nominated for Commissioner of the Election Assistance Commission. She is currently a Senior Trial Attorney in the Voting Section of the Civil Rights Division at the Department of Justice. McCormick has also served in various roles in the Office of the Attorney General of Virginia and as a Judicial Law Clerk.